VergilBench corpus — provenance + licenses

All 7 contracts in the Phase 3 seed corpus are Vergil-authored, Apache-2.0
single-file simplifications conformant with their reference standards.
No external code is vendored at this point.

Sources:
* erc20 → examples/erc20 (Vergil-authored, Apache-2.0)
* erc20-burnable, erc20-pausable → tests/kill_criterion_month2/project/src
  (Vergil-authored, Apache-2.0; semantically conformant with OpenZeppelin
  ERC20Burnable / ERC20Pausable for the verified properties)
* erc721 → examples/erc721 (Vergil-authored, Apache-2.0)
* vault-4626 → examples/vault-4626 (Vergil-authored, Apache-2.0)
* amm-constant-product → examples/amm-constant-product
  (Vergil-authored, Apache-2.0; semantically a Uniswap-V2-style pair with
  inlined accounting; not derived from Uniswap source)
* lending → examples/lending (Vergil-authored, Apache-2.0; Compound-style
  surface, simplified semantics)

Phase 4 will vendor or re-author external contracts (OpenZeppelin MIT,
Certora examples, Code4rena/Sherlock public sources). All external
vendoring goes through a license-diligence pass; nothing GPL / AGPL /
BUSL lands in `vergilbench/contracts/`.
